ureaucracy and short on teaching staff. I thought in a Democratic society we were allowed to make choices. Many school systems complain of overcrowding where would all the private and home schoolers go. The problem is not working parents who sacrifice to put their children through private schools it is the lack of leadership in the government and the public school system. Some smaller poorer states IE: Vermont have top flight public education. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="755" language="en" documentId="3960" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="vtrich" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:07PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="8" thumbsDown="0" origId="3960" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="755"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>